<span id="iv.iv.iv.i-p76"></span> “The act of knowing and comprehending
all things necessarily includes the expression of mind-work or wisdom,
that is, the Word, and without this it cannot even be conceived of.
Rightly, then, did the Fathers deduce the eternity of the Word from the
eternity of the Father.”—Hurter, *ad loc.*

